---
import Navbar from '../components/Navbar.astro';
import '../styles/landing.css';
---

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
  <title>Data Landing Zone &mdash; DevEx, Finance, Compliance. Balanced by design.</title>
  <meta name="description" content="An opinionated AWS landing zone for AI and data workloads, with security, privacy, and cost governance owned by the platform rather than each team." />
  <link rel="icon" href="/favicon.svg" type="image/svg+xml" />

  <meta property="og:title" content="Data Landing Zone" />
  <meta property="og:description" content="DevEx, Finance, Compliance. Balanced by design." />
  <meta property="og:image" content="/dlz-dark-og.png" />

  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com" />
  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin />
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Poppins:wght@300;400;500;600&display=swap" />

  <script is:inline>
    (function() {
      var stored = localStorage.getItem('starlight-theme');
      var prefersDark = window.matchMedia('(prefers-color-scheme: dark)').matches;
      var theme = stored || (prefersDark ? 'dark' : 'light');
      document.documentElement.classList.toggle('dark', theme === 'dark');
    })();
  </script>
</head>

<body class="dlz-page">

<Navbar />

<main>
<section class="dlz-section" style="z-index:8; position:relative;">
  <div class="dlz-full-row dlz-border-b">
    <div class="dlz-container">
      <div class="dlz-spacer-sm dlz-side-borders"></div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="dlz-full-row">
    <div class="dlz-container">
      <div class="dlz-hero-grid dlz-side-borders">
        <div class="dlz-hero-text">
          <p class="dlz-eyebrow" data-hero-anim style="animation-delay:0.1s">Data Landing Zone</p>
          <h1 class="dlz-hero-title" data-hero-anim style="animation-delay:0.25s">DevEx, Finance, Compliance.<br />Balanced by design.</h1>
          <p class="dlz-hero-body" data-hero-anim style="animation-delay:0.4s">
            After working across large AWS environments with hundreds of accounts, we saw the same tension again and again:<br />
            <span class="dlz-highlight">finance</span> wants control, <span class="dlz-highlight">compliance</span> wants certainty, and <span class="dlz-highlight">engineers</span> want speed.
          </p>
          <p class="dlz-hero-subline" data-hero-anim style="animation-delay:0.5s">
            Everyone told us to pick one.<br />
            <span class="dlz-highlight dlz-hero-punchline">We didn&rsquo;t.</span>
          </p>
          <div class="dlz-hero-ctas" data-hero-anim style="animation-delay:0.65s">
            <a href="/introduction" class="dlz-btn-primary">
              Introduction
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><path d="m9 18 6-6-6-6"></path></svg>
            </a>
            <a href="/getting-started" class="dlz-btn-ghost-hero">Get Started</a>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="dlz-hero-panel" data-hero-anim style="animation-delay:0.35s">
          <img src="/images/hero-panel-light.svg" alt="DevEx, Finance, Compliance balance diagram" class="dlz-hero-diagram dlz-diagram-light" fetchpriority="high" />
          <img src="/images/hero-panel-dark.svg"  alt="DevEx, Finance, Compliance balance diagram" class="dlz-hero-diagram dlz-diagram-dark"  fetchpriority="high" />
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="dlz-full-row dlz-border-t">
    <div class="dlz-container">
      <div class="dlz-spacer-xs dlz-side-borders"></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="dlz-section dlz-border-t" style="z-index:7; padding: 160px 0;">
  <div class="dlz-container dlz-px">
    <div class="dlz-prose-wide">
      <h2 class="dlz-section-title-lg" data-anim>The problem</h2>
      <p class="dlz-body-lg" data-anim data-delay="120">
        Cloud bills double overnight. Privacy audits land badly. Every workload reinvents the same governance, and engineers ship slower for it. By the time anyone notices the pattern, the architecture has already hardened around it, and remediation means changing things teams now depend on.
      </p>
      <p class="dlz-body-lg" data-anim data-delay="240" style="margin-top: 0;">
        The order is predictable. Privacy gets addressed first because regulation forces the conversation. FinOps gets addressed last, after the first billing shock. AI is now landing in the same sequence, except the spend curve is steeper than the regulatory one.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="dlz-section dlz-border-t" style="z-index:6;">
  <div class="dlz-full-row">
    <div class="dlz-container">
      <div class="dlz-quote-box dlz-side-borders">
        <div class="dlz-quote-inner">
          <p class="dlz-quote-text" data-anim>
            &ldquo;Surveyed companies reported average monthly AI budgets rising <span class="dlz-highlight">36%</span> in 2025, with only <span class="dlz-highlight">51%</span> confident they can measure the ROI of that spend.&rdquo;
          </p>
          <div class="dlz-quote-attr" data-anim data-delay="200">
            <p class="dlz-quote-source">CloudZero</p>
            <p class="dlz-quote-subtitle">The State of AI Costs, May 2025</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="dlz-section dlz-accent-border-t" style="z-index:5;">
  <div class="dlz-full-row">
    <div class="dlz-container">
      <div class="dlz-bridge-wrap">
        <p class="dlz-bridge-text" data-typing>The Data Landing Zone closes these gaps before the first workload lands.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="dlz-section dlz-accent-border-t" style="z-index:4;">
  <div class="dlz-full-row dlz-accent-border-t">
    <div class="dlz-container">
      <div class="dlz-spacer-md dlz-accent-side-borders"></div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="dlz-full-row dlz-accent-border-t" style="padding: 32px 0;">
    <div class="dlz-container dlz-px">
      <div class="dlz-section-header" data-anim>
        <h2 class="dlz-section-title-xl">Built for three stakeholders at once</h2>
        <p class="dlz-section-subtitle">Data platforms usually pick one of these audiences to serve well. The DLZ aims to serve all three.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="dlz-full-row dlz-accent-border-t dlz-accent-border-b">
    <div class="dlz-container dlz-px" style="padding-top: 24px; padding-bottom: 24px;">
      <div class="dlz-three-cols">
        <div class="dlz-stakeholder-col">
          <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="48" height="48" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="dlz-stake-icon" aria-hidden="true"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"></circle><path d="M16 8h-6a2 2 0 1 0 0 4h4a2 2 0 1 1 0 4H8"></path><path d="M12 18V6"></path></svg>
          <h3 class="dlz-stake-title">CFO &amp; Finance</h3>
          <p class="dlz-stake-desc">Cost attribution is part of provisioning. Budgets and anomaly alerts ship as code alongside the workload they monitor, and every resource carries the tags needed to roll spend up to a team, product, or environment. Chargeback becomes a query rather than a reconciliation project.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="dlz-stakeholder-col">
          <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="48" height="48" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="dlz-stake-icon" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M12 7v14"></path><path d="M16 12h2"></path><path d="M16 8h2"></path><path d="M3 18a1 1 0 0 1-1-1V4a1 1 0 0 1 1-1h5a4 4 0 0 1 4 4 4 4 0 0 1 4-4h5a1 1 0 0 1 1 1v13a1 1 0 0 1-1 1h-6a3 3 0 0 0-3 3 3 3 0 0 0-3-3z"></path><path d="M6 12h2"></path><path d="M6 8h2"></path></svg>
          <h3 class="dlz-stake-title">Compliance Office</h3>
          <p class="dlz-stake-desc">The controls regulators look for are owned by the platform: GDPR alignment, data classification, access logging, audit trails. When an audit lands, the evidence is already in the same place it was last quarter.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="dlz-stakeholder-col">
          <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="48" height="48" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="dlz-stake-icon" aria-hidden="true"><path d="m18 16 4-4-4-4"></path><path d="m6 8-4 4 4 4"></path><path d="m14.5 4-5 16"></path></svg>
          <h3 class="dlz-stake-title">Engineers</h3>
          <p class="dlz-stake-desc">Engineers get a paved road. Common requests like a new account, a new pipeline, or access to a dataset resolve through self-service against guardrails the platform already enforces. Policy is checked at deploy and audit time, so PRs don&rsquo;t run into governance walls in the middle of code review.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="dlz-full-row dlz-accent-border-t">
    <div class="dlz-container dlz-px" style="padding-top: 24px; padding-bottom: 24px;">
      <div class="dlz-design-principle-wrap" data-anim>
        <h4 class="dlz-design-principle-label">Design principle.</h4>
        <p class="dlz-design-principle-text">The compliant path should be the convenient one. When following policy is the fastest way to ship, engineers do it by default, and working around it stops being worth the effort.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="dlz-full-row dlz-accent-border-t">
    <div class="dlz-container">
      <div class="dlz-spacer-md dlz-accent-side-borders"></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="dlz-section dlz-accent-border-t dlz-finops-section" style="z-index:3;">
  <div class="dlz-container dlz-px">
    <div class="dlz-finops-grid">
      <div class="dlz-finops-left">
        <div class="dlz-finops-left-inner">
          <h2 class="dlz-finops-title" data-anim>How the DLZ delivers on FinOps</h2>
          <p class="dlz-finops-subtitle" data-anim data-delay="100">FinOps tends to arrive last, after the first billing shock makes it urgent. The DLZ ships the cost-management capability ready to use, in four layers.</p>
          <a href="/introduction" class="dlz-btn-finops" data-anim data-delay="200">
            Introduction
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><path d="m9 18 6-6-6-6"></path></svg>
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="dlz-finops-right">
        <div class="dlz-finops-item">
          <div class="dlz-finops-item-icon"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="40" height="40" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M13 5h8"></path><path d="M13 12h8"></path><path d="M13 19h8"></path><path d="m3 17 2 2 4-4"></path><path d="m3 7 2 2 4-4"></path></svg></div>
          <div class="dlz-finops-item-text">
            <h3 class="dlz-finops-item-title">Instrumentation</h3>
            <p class="dlz-finops-item-desc">Every service emits cost and usage data in a consistent form. CUR 2.0 is the system of record, written to a dedicated FinOps account and queryable from Athena.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="dlz-finops-separator"></div>
        <div class="dlz-finops-item">
          <div class="dlz-finops-item-icon"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="40" height="40" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M17 3a2 2 0 0 1 2 2v15a1 1 0 0 1-1.496.868l-4.512-2.578a2 2 0 0 0-1.984 0l-4.512 2.578A1 1 0 0 1 5 20V5a2 2 0 0 1 2-2z"></path><path d="m9 10 2 2 4-4"></path></svg></div>
          <div class="dlz-finops-item-text">
            <h3 class="dlz-finops-item-title">Attribution</h3>
            <p class="dlz-finops-item-desc">A mandatory tag set is enforced at deploy time. Tag policies, SCPs, and DLZ-side validation all check it before a resource ships. Anything that can&rsquo;t be attributed to an owner doesn&rsquo;t reach production.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="dlz-finops-separator"></div>
        <div class="dlz-finops-item">
          <div class="dlz-finops-item-icon"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="40" height="40" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M20 13c0 5-3.5 7.5-7.66 8.95a1 1 0 0 1-.67-.01C7.5 20.5 4 18 4 13V6a1 1 0 0 1 1-1c2 0 4.5-1.2 6.24-2.72a1.17 1.17 0 0 1 1.52 0C14.51 3.81 17 5 19 5a1 1 0 0 1 1 1z"></path><path d="m9 12 2 2 4-4"></path></svg></div>
          <div class="dlz-finops-item-text">
            <h3 class="dlz-finops-item-title">Guardrails</h3>
            <p class="dlz-finops-item-desc">Budgets alert when usage approaches the threshold and stop spend when it crosses the limit. An LLM gateway applies per-team and per-project token caps in real time, so a runaway agent burns minutes of budget rather than days.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="dlz-finops-separator"></div>
        <div class="dlz-finops-item">
          <div class="dlz-finops-item-icon"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="40" height="40" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M16 7h6v6"></path><path d="m22 7-8.5 8.5-5-5L2 17"></path></svg></div>
          <div class="dlz-finops-item-text">
            <h3 class="dlz-finops-item-title">Reporting</h3>
            <p class="dlz-finops-item-desc">Each role gets the view it needs: engineers see service-level burn, product owners see feature cost, finance sees the chargeback rollup. Cost-per-unit-of-work turns &ldquo;we should optimise&rdquo; into a number.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="dlz-section" style="z-index:2;">
  <div class="dlz-full-row dlz-accent-border-t dlz-accent-border-b">
    <div class="dlz-container">
      <div class="dlz-spacer-lg dlz-accent-side-borders"></div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="dlz-full-row dlz-accent-border-t" style="padding: 32px 0 48px;">
    <div class="dlz-container dlz-px">
      <h2 class="dlz-section-title-xl" data-anim>What is the Data Landing Zone?</h2>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="dlz-full-row dlz-accent-border-t dlz-accent-border-b">
    <div class="dlz-container">
      <div class="dlz-features-grid dlz-accent-side-borders">
        <div class="dlz-feature-col dlz-feature-col-right-border">
          <div class="dlz-feature-item dlz-feature-border-b">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="40" height="40" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="dlz-feature-icon" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M12 15v5s3.03-.55 4-2c1.08-1.62 0-5 0-5"></path><path d="M4.5 16.5c-1.5 1.26-2 5-2 5s3.74-.5 5-2c.71-.84.7-2.13-.09-2.91a2.18 2.18 0 0 0-2.91-.09"></path><path d="M9 12a22 22 0 0 1 2-3.95A12.88 12.88 0 0 1 22 2c0 2.72-.78 7.5-6 11a22.4 22.4 0 0 1-4 2z"></path><path d="M9 12H4s.55-3.03 2-4c1.62-1.08 5 .05 5 .05"></path></svg>
            <h3 class="dlz-feature-title">Accelerator</h3>
            <p class="dlz-feature-desc">A landing zone tailored for AI, data-driven, data mesh, and cloud projects, so teams can experiment fast without building governance from scratch.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="dlz-feature-item dlz-feature-border-b">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="40" height="40" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="dlz-feature-icon" aria-hidden="true"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"></circle><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="6"></circle><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="2"></circle></svg>
            <h3 class="dlz-feature-title">All-in-one CDK component</h3>
            <p class="dlz-feature-desc">A CDK construct published in TypeScript and Python that orchestrates AWS accounts and the resources needed for a multi-account data platform.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="dlz-feature-item dlz-feature-border-b">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="40" height="40" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="dlz-feature-icon" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M20 13c0 5-3.5 7.5-7.66 8.95a1 1 0 0 1-.67-.01C7.5 20.5 4 18 4 13V6a1 1 0 0 1 1-1c2 0 4.5-1.2 6.24-2.72a1.17 1.17 0 0 1 1.52 0C14.51 3.81 17 5 19 5a1 1 0 0 1 1 1z"></path><path d="m9 12 2 2 4-4"></path></svg>
            <h3 class="dlz-feature-title">Standards &amp; best practices</h3>
            <p class="dlz-feature-desc">Aligned with the AWS Well-Architected Framework for multi-account strategy, security, and compliance.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="dlz-feature-col dlz-feature-col-offset">
          <div class="dlz-feature-item dlz-feature-border-t dlz-feature-border-b">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="40" height="40" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="dlz-feature-icon" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M6 22a2 2 0 0 1-2-2V4a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h8a2.4 2.4 0 0 1 1.704.706l3.588 3.588A2.4 2.4 0 0 1 20 8v12a2 2 0 0 1-2 2z"></path><path d="M14 2v5a1 1 0 0 0 1 1h5"></path><path d="M12 12v6"></path><path d="m15 15-3-3-3 3"></path></svg>
            <h3 class="dlz-feature-title">Lessons in the defaults</h3>
            <p class="dlz-feature-desc">Years of operational lessons about regulators, billing, and incident response are encoded as defaults in the platform. New workloads inherit them without anyone having to remember to apply them.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="dlz-feature-item dlz-feature-border-b">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="40" height="40" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="dlz-feature-icon" aria-hidden="true"><ellipse cx="12" cy="5" rx="9" ry="3"></ellipse><path d="M3 5V19A9 3 0 0 0 21 19V5"></path><path d="M3 12A9 3 0 0 0 21 12"></path></svg>
            <h3 class="dlz-feature-title">FinOps as a platform concern</h3>
            <p class="dlz-feature-desc">Mandatory cost-allocation tags enforced at deploy time. Budgets and anomaly controls as code. CUR centralised in a dedicated FinOps account. An LLM gateway that blocks token spend before it reaches the model.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="dlz-feature-item">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="40" height="40" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="dlz-feature-icon" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M2 9.5a5.5 5.5 0 0 1 9.591-3.676.56.56 0 0 0 .818 0A5.49 5.49 0 0 1 22 9.5c0 2.29-1.5 4-3 5.5l-5.492 5.313a2 2 0 0 1-3 .019L5 15c-1.5-1.5-3-3.2-3-5.5"></path></svg>
            <h3 class="dlz-feature-title">Ease of use</h3>
            <p class="dlz-feature-desc">Data engineers can deploy it using the defaults. Cloud engineers can customise the parts their organisation needs to fine-tune.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="dlz-full-row dlz-accent-border-t dlz-accent-border-b">
    <div class="dlz-container">
      <div class="dlz-spacer-lg dlz-accent-side-borders"></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
</main>

<footer class="dlz-footer dlz-border-t" style="z-index:1;">
  <div class="dlz-footer-inner">
